Live 2019 Election Turnout Tracker

Welcome to the Sixty-Six Wards turnout tracker! Voters across Philadelphia are sharing their turnout to support citizen science.

First, vote! Then, share your division and Voter Number at http://bit.ly/sixtysixturnout.

Live Results

As of 02:48, 500 voters in 65 wards have shared their voter number. I estimate that 112,366 people have voted across the city (95% Confidence Interval: 107,074 - 119,104).

Maps

I use historic correlations among divisions’ turnout to estimate turnout in the divisions with no data yet. I simultaneously estimate (1) the overall city-wide turnout, (2) divisions’ over-/under-performance, and (3) the city-wide time pattern of voting.
